===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|oeconomia|lang=la}} from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|οἰκονομία||management of a househould, administration|tr=oikonomia|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}} from {{term|οἶκος||house|tr=oikos|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}} + {{term|νόμος||law|tr=nomos|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}}.  The first recorded sense of the word "economy", found in a work possibly composed in 1440, is "the management of economic affairs", in this case, of a monastery.

